this market is brutal to say the least!! Lay offs of tech people left and right! So far i have one great lead ... as ramp manager for a small airline in Tampa. I've been out of the aircraft field for 5 years now but they are still interested. I have a free ticket coming from Delta so I'm thinking about flying out this week for a face to face interview. If I get lucky and land this job it would be a great load off my shoulders! I'll keep everyone posted!!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/uceleroy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celeroy</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(4/25/01 5:53:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=565.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Final nail in the coffin </span><hr size=1> Hey all~<br>
<br>
I received this mail from Rick late last night and he wanted me to share it with you. Here's to Pirating, may his sails be always windward. Good luck Rick, see you asap.<br>
<br>
<br>
Well, I got knocked on my butt. I'm still fighting but by the time I got back on my feet the fight was over ... now there is just the aftermath to deal with.<br>
<br>
1) 2 paychecks bounced<br>
2) Travel advance bounced<br>
3) Out of time<br>
4) Out of money<br>
<br>
I was hoping that I would have a month to stay put and find another job as my resumes did their work but I just can't stay now that I just found out I have zero dollars left.<br>
<br>
Eric and the company really did a number on a lot of people. 50 people out of work, 2 of our vendors are going down because of all the credit they extended us that will never be repaid, and I'm on the move.<br>
<br>
I'll be flying to Tampa Wednesday morning for a few interviews at blue collar, low level, places but hopefully I can land something to at least begin again. I'll fly back Thursday night, give away all the furniture Friday and drive back to Tampa on Saturday. My sister is going to let me live there until I can get back on my feet again.<br>
<br>
Damn, here I am at 38 having to start all over again in life. Dia's lifestyle sure sounds good right about now. But I tell you what ... never again!!! Never will I be totally dependent on someone else for a paycheck. I have plans that will go into effect as soon as I begin working again. <br>
<br>
Going to be an interesting change but hell, I've been a Boy Scout, a G.I., a Man of God and now in Florida I'll be a Pirate!!<br>
<br>
The FTFL site is down but please cut and paste this for everyone if you can.<br>
<br>
Hopefully this summer I'll be back in game to relax so DON'T DISBAND my friends. Crow will rise again!!<br>
<br>
<br>
Rick Lange<br>
